02:37.230 --> 02:38.950
Do I seem crazy to you?

02:40.350 --> 02:44.030
Crazy for not having screamed
everything that my breast yearns for?

02:44.600 --> 02:45.990
They are coming!

03:13.230 --> 03:16.490
I have to contain myself
so as not to stab you with...

03:19.640 --> 03:20.850
Let her go!

03:22.430 --> 03:24.440
I came so she could kill me.

03:33.350 --> 03:35.740
Because I went with
the other one.

03:37.230 --> 03:38.320
I went.

03:45.390 --> 03:47.440
You would have done the same.

03:49.640 --> 03:51.640
I was a woman scorned,

03:52.930 --> 03:55.440
full of shame both inside and out.

03:58.560 --> 03:59.900
And your son...

04:02.850 --> 04:05.280
Your son he was the hope...

04:05.350 --> 04:10.490
I had for children,
for land... for strength.

04:12.480 --> 04:13.900
But the other,

04:15.600 --> 04:18.490
the other was a dark river,
full of bracken,

04:21.140 --> 04:23.890
that brought me the murmur
of it's reeds

04:24.230 --> 04:26.820
and song between clenched teeth.

04:32.520 --> 04:34.070
I didn't want to...

04:35.100 --> 04:38.240
Do you hear me? I didn't want to...

04:40.180 --> 04:42.270
Your son was my life.

04:44.890 --> 04:48.190
But the embrace of another
dragged me down like a tidal wave.

04:49.230 --> 04:51.650
Like the butt of a mule...

04:52.180 --> 04:54.530
And he could have dragged
me down forever.

04:56.480 --> 04:57.860
Forever...

05:00.060 --> 05:01.400
Forever...

07:23.180 --> 07:26.890
<i>Out of the four muleteers.</i>

07:27.640 --> 07:31.690
<i>Out of the four muleteers.</i>

07:31.730 --> 07:34.900
<i>Out of the four muleteers.</i>

07:35.350 --> 07:38.599
<i>Oh mommy, going to the water,</i>

07:38.600 --> 07:40.860
<i>going to the water.</i>

07:42.390 --> 07:46.350
<i>The one on the dapple-grey mule.</i>

07:46.770 --> 07:50.320
<i>The one on the dapple-grey mule.</i>

07:50.480 --> 07:53.139
<i>The one on the dapple-grey mule.</i>

07:53.140 --> 07:57.639
<i>Oh mommy, is stealing my soul,</i>

07:57.640 --> 08:00.020
<i>is stealing my soul.</i>

08:00.140 --> 08:04.730
<i>It is raining in the fields.</i>

08:04.810 --> 08:08.240
<i>It is raining in the fields.</i>

08:08.560 --> 08:11.990
<i>Oh mommy, my love gets wet,</i>

08:12.390 --> 08:14.600
<i>my love gets wet.</i>

08:15.730 --> 08:19.530
<i>Who could be a little tree.</i>

08:20.270 --> 08:23.450
<i>Who could be a little tree.</i>

08:24.640 --> 08:28.560
<i>Oh mommy, full of leaves,</i>

08:28.560 --> 08:30.650
<i>full of leaves.</i>

08:31.890 --> 08:36.480
<i>Ay, better keep quiet.</i>

08:46.060 --> 08:47.070
Whoa!

09:03.980 --> 09:06.240
What are you doing?
They will see us...

09:06.430 --> 09:07.810
Get off, get off...

09:12.480 --> 09:16.280
Stop, no, no, no stop!

09:16.600 --> 09:17.950
No, no, no...!

09:25.600 --> 09:28.900
Look young one,
the tablecloths have arrived.

09:31.890 --> 09:34.429
Have you ever seen such linen?

09:34.430 --> 09:35.890
And the embroidery?

09:37.310 --> 09:39.269
- You can tell it's your mother's work.
- My mother!

09:39.270 --> 09:42.170
I am going to fetch
her before she notices I am late.

10:00.390 --> 10:04.390
<i>Lullaby, baby, lullaby...</i>

10:05.480 --> 10:09.820
<i>About the horse...</i>

10:11.390 --> 10:15.230
that didn't want to drink...

10:25.430 --> 10:28.060
Look... an apple.

10:29.100 --> 10:30.820
He is perfect today.

10:31.930 --> 10:33.140
And you?

10:34.350 --> 10:35.349
I have spent two months

10:35.350 --> 10:38.800
putting new shoes on the horse
and they are always coming loose.

10:42.560 --> 10:44.900
The stones pull them off.

10:50.770 --> 10:52.990
Or maybe it is just overworked?

10:53.680 --> 10:54.770
No.

10:57.640 --> 10:59.640
I don't use him that much.

11:02.180 --> 11:06.280
The neighbours told me that yesterday
they saw you on the edge of the plains;

11:07.770 --> 11:09.450
- was that you?
- No.

11:13.390 --> 11:14.350
Hey...

11:15.770 --> 11:18.070
I was with the wheat overseers.

11:19.100 --> 11:21.000
They are always so entertaining.

11:23.810 --> 11:25.700
I need a new dress.

11:26.390 --> 11:30.270
- And the baby a new cap.
- So who has been racing that horse?

11:31.560 --> 11:34.349
He is downstairs with his eyes
popping out his head,

11:34.350 --> 11:36.650
like he has seen
the end of the world.

11:37.430 --> 11:38.690
Me...

11:39.730 --> 11:41.360
I did that.

11:41.930 --> 11:43.100
Of course.

11:44.270 --> 11:45.700
He's yours.

11:51.980 --> 11:54.900
Did you know they are asking
for my cousin's hand?

11:55.430 --> 11:56.690
When?

11:59.270 --> 12:00.400
Today.

12:01.230 --> 12:04.880
I think the mother of the groom
is not very happy about the wedding.

12:05.020 --> 12:07.820
She's right.
That girl can't be trusted.

12:54.140 --> 12:55.310
My daughter.

12:56.520 --> 12:57.700
Father...

13:02.350 --> 13:03.820
Are you happy?

13:06.520 --> 13:08.400
The wine is here.

13:09.060 --> 13:10.200
I'm coming.

13:24.060 --> 13:26.320
Congratulations young one,

13:27.730 --> 13:29.450
on your engagement...

13:32.350 --> 13:34.849
- Thank you.
- What's the matter child?

13:34.850 --> 13:36.650
Aren't you happy?

13:39.390 --> 13:42.140
- Who are you?
- I bring you a gift...

13:42.270 --> 13:43.950
and some advice.

13:44.480 --> 13:45.650
What?

14:00.770 --> 14:02.650
With a knife,

14:03.730 --> 14:07.530
with a small knife
that barely fits in your hand,

14:09.480 --> 14:13.740
but cuts like ice,
into astonished flesh,

14:14.270 --> 14:16.280
and there it stays,

14:16.810 --> 14:24.490
where the dark root of the scream
quivers and snarls.

14:26.350 --> 14:29.700
Who are you?
What are you doing here?

14:30.140 --> 14:33.440
Don't get married,
if you don't love him.

14:38.270 --> 14:40.650
Get out... get out of this house!

15:27.810 --> 15:33.450
<i>Lullaby, my baby, lullaby</i>

15:37.560 --> 15:47.280
<i>once there was a big horse</i>

15:51.270 --> 15:58.570
<i>who didn't like water</i>

16:01.680 --> 16:08.730
<i>Who didn't like water</i>

16:11.640 --> 16:17.940
<i>The water was black there</i>

16:20.230 --> 16:26.610
<i>under the branches</i>

16:29.060 --> 16:35.860
<i>When it reached the bridge</i>

16:37.770 --> 16:44.740
<i>it stopped and it sang</i>

17:00.060 --> 17:06.819
<i>Who can say, my baby,</i>

17:10.310 --> 17:17.780
<i>what the stream holds</i>

17:20.849 --> 17:27.609
<i>with it's long tail</i>

17:30.230 --> 17:37.900
<i>in it's green parlor</i>

18:28.020 --> 18:29.110
How are you?

18:30.980 --> 18:33.130
I closed up shop and came to see you.

18:33.680 --> 18:35.309
We live so far from each other!

18:35.310 --> 18:37.639
It's been 20 years since
I went to the top end of the street.

18:37.640 --> 18:40.310
- Are you ok?
- What do you think?

18:41.520 --> 18:43.809
Two days ago they brought
in my neighbour's son

18:43.810 --> 18:46.360
with his two arms
cut up by the machine.

18:46.680 --> 18:47.890
Rafael?

18:48.560 --> 18:51.780
Yes, and there he is.

18:54.140 --> 18:57.230
I think about my son often,
and yours...

18:57.930 --> 19:00.810
they are better off where they are.
Sleeping,

19:02.810 --> 19:04.700
- resting.
- Enough!

19:05.350 --> 19:08.280
That is conjecture, it doesn't help.

19:08.560 --> 19:09.849
Months have passed

19:09.850 --> 19:13.500
and my still sadness stings my eyes
and even the strands of my hair.

19:14.060 --> 19:18.360
When I finally got to see my son,
I soaked my hands in his blood...

19:20.140 --> 19:22.519
and then licked them with my tongue.

19:22.520 --> 19:25.740
Because he was mine.
You wouldn't understand that...

19:25.890 --> 19:28.480
- Madam!
- I will never be still.

19:34.600 --> 19:36.450
You still have one left.

19:38.020 --> 19:39.740
Think about it.

19:39.890 --> 19:42.429
What are you doing here instead
of coming with me to the vineyards?

19:42.430 --> 19:44.269
And what would an old woman
do in a vineyard?

19:44.270 --> 19:45.450
Old?

19:46.600 --> 19:49.200
Old? Yes, so, so old!

19:51.310 --> 19:53.860
Your father used to take me there...

19:53.890 --> 19:56.059
So he finally bought that vineyard?

19:56.060 --> 19:57.400
He got lucky.

19:57.640 --> 19:59.480
Now he's getting married.

20:01.230 --> 20:03.429
Do you know my son's fiancée?

20:03.430 --> 20:04.889
She's a fine girl.

20:04.890 --> 20:06.350
Yes, but...

20:08.680 --> 20:11.020
You can never know
anyone deep inside.

20:11.270 --> 20:12.780
But she's nice.

20:12.930 --> 20:16.940
She lives alone with her father
out there, so far away...

20:17.480 --> 20:19.450
she's used to solitude.

20:20.060 --> 20:21.610
And her mother?

20:21.730 --> 20:24.280
She was beautiful.
But I never liked her.

20:25.060 --> 20:28.019
- She didn't love her husband.
- But everyone knows too much!

20:28.020 --> 20:29.900
You were the one who asked!

20:30.140 --> 20:31.940
Has she ever had a boyfriend?

20:33.020 --> 20:34.990
When she was 15 years old.

20:35.230 --> 20:38.240
But a few years ago he got married
to her cousin.

20:38.480 --> 20:41.430
- Nobody remembers the engagement...
- And who was he?

20:42.770 --> 20:43.929
Leonardo.

20:43.930 --> 20:45.310
Which Leonardo?

20:48.060 --> 20:49.490
Leonardo Felix.

20:52.310 --> 20:53.570
Felix!

20:59.640 --> 21:02.100
You know that my financée
is a good girl.

21:02.980 --> 21:04.780
- Yes.
- So?

21:05.230 --> 21:07.740
Yes... I am not sure what I am saying.

21:07.770 --> 21:10.309
I know that she is hard-working and good.
But despite that,

21:10.310 --> 21:13.820
when you mention her name
it's like throwing a rock at my head.

21:14.270 --> 21:15.450
I should go.

21:15.810 --> 21:18.460
My people from the fields
will be arriving soon.

21:20.980 --> 21:23.519
Don't get in the way
of your son's happiness.

21:23.520 --> 21:25.900
It's time for us to step back now.

21:32.350 --> 21:35.200
Don't pay heed.
I know you will love my fiancée.

21:36.850 --> 21:38.110
I will.

21:40.890 --> 21:43.600
It's just that... I will be alone.

21:43.930 --> 21:45.690
First it was your father...

21:47.640 --> 21:51.480
whom I loved with all my heart.
And that lasted barely three years.

21:52.020 --> 21:53.570
Then your brother...

21:57.350 --> 21:59.530
and now there is only you.

22:00.640 --> 22:02.310
I don't want you to go.

22:07.600 --> 22:09.280
Yes, yes, yes...

22:10.730 --> 22:12.900
I know you are too old for kisses.

22:13.230 --> 22:15.389
Let's see if you lighten up my life
with six grandchildren.

22:15.390 --> 22:18.980
Or however many you want.
Your father never gave me any.

22:19.230 --> 22:20.990
The first one for you.

22:21.520 --> 22:24.099
- But let it be a girl.
- Get ready.

22:24.100 --> 22:26.200
It's a long road ahead.

22:31.100 --> 22:32.150
Go!

23:30.930 --> 23:33.480
- Was it a long trip?
- Four hours.

23:33.730 --> 23:36.030
Well you took the long road.

23:37.060 --> 23:39.780
I am too old to travel
by the river banks.

23:39.890 --> 23:41.270
She gets dizzy.

23:43.100 --> 23:44.360
Come in.

23:46.180 --> 23:47.809
Nice crop of esparto grass.

23:47.810 --> 23:50.769
In my time, there was no esparto
grass around here.

23:50.770 --> 23:55.929
Now we need to beat it with a stick
almost, to get anything out of it.

23:55.930 --> 23:58.389
But now it is giving you a return.
Stop complaining.

23:58.390 --> 24:00.429
I haven't come to ask you
for anything.

24:00.430 --> 24:01.979
You are richer than I am.

24:01.980 --> 24:04.900
Vineyards are worth
a pretty penny. Wine?

24:05.390 --> 24:06.560
No...

24:08.640 --> 24:11.730
I am just sorry that our lands
are separate.

24:11.980 --> 24:16.559
If only we could bring your vineyards
here with 20 pairs of oxen

24:16.560 --> 24:18.769
and put them together on the slope.

24:18.770 --> 24:20.429
- What joy!
- What for?

24:20.430 --> 24:23.479
When I die, you'll sell it
and buy the land next door.

24:23.480 --> 24:28.280
Sell? Why? no!
I would buy it, buy it all.

24:39.140 --> 24:42.810
Son, go fetch her.
We have things to talk about.

24:58.680 --> 25:01.270
- You know why I have come.
- Yes.

25:01.520 --> 25:02.700
And?

25:03.020 --> 25:06.030
It seems like a good idea,
they have spoken about it.

25:08.520 --> 25:10.700
My son is willing and able.

25:10.930 --> 25:12.810
So is my daughter.

25:20.480 --> 25:21.740
Greetings...

25:25.350 --> 25:26.700
Come closer.

25:33.930 --> 25:35.560
Are you happy?

25:36.140 --> 25:38.560
- Yes, yes I am.
- Of course you are.

25:41.060 --> 25:42.400
Look at me.

25:47.930 --> 25:50.520
She looks so much like my wife did.

25:55.100 --> 25:56.990
How lovely you are!

25:58.430 --> 26:00.980
Do you understand
what marriage means child?

26:01.890 --> 26:03.019
Yes, madam.

26:03.020 --> 26:07.990
A husband, children and a two-yard
thick wall between everything else.

26:10.730 --> 26:12.530
I will not disappoint.

26:12.680 --> 26:15.350
Of course, of course you won't.

26:17.890 --> 26:19.850
Here are your gifts.

26:23.310 --> 26:24.450
Thank you.

26:28.810 --> 26:29.950
Come.

26:35.520 --> 26:38.150
My mother wanted me
to give you this present.

26:46.680 --> 26:48.100
They are antique.

26:49.060 --> 26:50.450
Made of brass.

26:52.100 --> 26:53.530
Do you like them?

27:05.310 --> 27:08.019
When I am by your side
I feel so proud.

27:08.020 --> 27:09.809
It brings a lump to my throat.

27:09.810 --> 27:12.490
When we are married
that will disappear.

27:15.140 --> 27:18.140
I am longing to be your wife,
to be alone with you...

27:19.140 --> 27:21.730
and not hear anyone
else's voice but yours.

27:22.770 --> 27:25.070
And only see your eyes.

27:26.350 --> 27:28.860
You hold me so tight, so tight,

27:30.930 --> 27:33.729
that if it were my mother
herself calling me,

27:33.730 --> 27:35.780
I couldn't let you go.

27:46.680 --> 27:48.390
I have strong arms.

27:48.640 --> 27:51.440
I will hold you for forty years
without letting go.

28:17.350 --> 28:21.700
<i>Skein, skein,</i>

28:22.350 --> 28:25.650
<i>what would you be?</i>

28:26.930 --> 28:30.640
<i>Dress of jasmine,</i>

28:31.730 --> 28:34.780
<i>tie of cristal.</i>

28:36.350 --> 28:41.240
<i>To be born at four,</i>

28:42.310 --> 28:45.280
<i>and to die at ten.</i>

28:45.930 --> 28:50.440
<i>A strand of wool,</i>

28:51.310 --> 28:54.990
<i>a chain at your feet,</i>

28:55.890 --> 28:58.980
<i>and a knot to bind</i>

28:59.520 --> 29:03.860
<i>the bitter laurel.</i>

29:05.350 --> 29:10.110
<i>Skein, skein,</i>

29:10.980 --> 29:14.530
<i>what would you say?</i>

29:15.350 --> 29:20.400
<i>A voiceless lover.</i>

29:21.520 --> 29:25.990
<i>A crimson husband.</i>

29:27.930 --> 29:29.479
You can't be inside in this heat.

29:29.480 --> 29:32.450
These lands don't cool down,
even at dawn.

29:36.770 --> 29:40.179
My mother was from a very green place.
From rich lands.

29:40.180 --> 29:42.560
She would have been happy there.

29:42.930 --> 29:44.020
Yes.

29:45.480 --> 29:47.530
But this place ate her up.

29:48.230 --> 29:50.110
As it does all of us.

29:50.730 --> 29:52.110
Destiny.

29:53.640 --> 29:54.810
Destiny.

29:58.600 --> 30:02.500
- The walls feel like they are on fire.
- You are going to look gorgeous.

30:02.980 --> 30:06.820
Oh lucky you, who is going
to embrace a man,

30:07.020 --> 30:10.639
kiss him, feel his weight by your side.

30:10.640 --> 30:11.850
Stop...

30:11.890 --> 30:16.100
The best is when you wake up,
when you feel him by your side and you

30:16.430 --> 30:19.560
- brush his shoulders with your breath.
- That's enough!

30:19.730 --> 30:20.979
But girl!

30:20.980 --> 30:25.400
That is what a wedding is,
and nothing more.

30:26.730 --> 30:29.860
A wedding is a bed, a man...

30:32.020 --> 30:33.530
and a woman.

30:34.640 --> 30:36.980
Don't overthink it.

30:38.140 --> 30:40.440
Or do you have your reasons?

30:41.310 --> 30:44.510
Could it be that you don't want
to get married? Say so now!

30:45.270 --> 30:47.450
You can still turn back.

30:49.140 --> 30:50.890
I just feel foggy.

30:52.140 --> 30:54.440
The stale air around here.

30:54.640 --> 30:56.850
Who doesn't have their doubts?

30:56.890 --> 30:58.890
Do you love your fiancée?

31:02.680 --> 31:05.440
Yes, of course I do.

31:13.310 --> 31:17.490
<i>A voiceless lover.</i>

31:18.680 --> 31:23.350
<i>A crimson husband.</i>

33:05.520 --> 33:07.720
- Long live the newlyweds!
- Long live!

33:10.520 --> 33:12.720
- Long live the newlyweds!
- Long live!

33:12.980 --> 33:15.180
- Long live the newlyweds!
- Long live!

33:32.390 --> 33:35.390
- They are also here?
- They are family.

33:36.180 --> 33:38.639
- Today is a day to forgive.
- I can bare them.

33:38.640 --> 33:41.390
- But I won't forgive them.
- Give it up...

33:42.890 --> 33:45.480
What has Leonardo ever done?

33:45.770 --> 33:46.900
True.

33:47.270 --> 33:51.220
But when I hear the name Felix, you
might as well fill my mouth with silt.

33:51.350 --> 33:54.400
- I have to spit so as not to kill...
- Behave yourself.

33:54.810 --> 33:56.400
What good will it do?

33:56.640 --> 33:59.520
None. But you understand.

34:01.480 --> 34:03.820
Can you bring anyone
back from the dead?

34:06.060 --> 34:07.530
And they preside.

34:07.680 --> 34:11.060
What does it mean to preside?
There they eat, smoke...

34:14.520 --> 34:16.309
You are right,
I need to keep my mouth shut.

34:16.310 --> 34:17.599
People will talk...

34:17.600 --> 34:20.030
What joy! My children!

34:21.230 --> 34:22.530
What joy!

34:28.600 --> 34:30.530
You look beautiful.

34:33.270 --> 34:34.860
Congratulations son.

34:42.020 --> 34:44.239
- There is much to celebrate.
- Yes.

35:35.100 --> 35:36.280
Thank you.

35:39.480 --> 35:42.280
- Let's go.
- No. You go ahead.

35:51.770 --> 35:52.950
Gorgeous!

36:11.310 --> 36:12.860
Congratulations.

36:23.100 --> 36:24.530
Why did you come?

36:26.480 --> 36:28.320
To see your wedding.

36:31.430 --> 36:32.979
I also saw yours.

36:32.980 --> 36:34.729
Still yearning for you.

36:34.730 --> 36:35.950
Lies.

36:40.730 --> 36:42.150
And your wife?

36:42.730 --> 36:45.150
This conversation has to stop.

36:49.850 --> 36:52.360
How come we can't talk to each other?

36:53.020 --> 36:54.360
She is right.

36:54.770 --> 36:57.610
- I shouldn't be talking to you.
- Hey, let's go!

37:00.020 --> 37:01.240
Let's go!

37:27.770 --> 37:30.150
What was I to you?

37:31.730 --> 37:32.900
Tell me.

37:33.140 --> 37:34.730
Think hard.

37:35.890 --> 37:38.480
Two mules and a run-down
shack wasn't much.

37:42.100 --> 37:43.610
Almost nothing at all.

37:45.020 --> 37:47.610
Go and wait for your wife
by the door.

37:50.230 --> 37:51.530
And the bride?

38:00.890 --> 38:05.270
After I got married I thought night
and day about whose fault it was,

38:05.270 --> 38:09.280
and each time the guilty
part swapped.

38:31.020 --> 38:32.860
But fault there was.

38:38.230 --> 38:39.570
It's too late.

38:49.680 --> 38:52.100
A man with a horse is wise...

38:54.640 --> 38:59.310
and capable enough to wrench out
a young girl stuck in the desert.

39:01.890 --> 39:03.730
But I have my pride.

39:04.930 --> 39:06.639
And that's why I got married.

39:06.640 --> 39:10.890
I will wall myself in with my husband,
whom I will love for the rest of my life.

39:12.230 --> 39:14.280
Pride won't help you.

39:18.100 --> 39:19.740
Don't come near me.

39:20.810 --> 39:25.570
Bitterness is the worst
punishment of all.

39:27.640 --> 39:31.269
What good does pride
do if I can't gaze at you,

39:31.270 --> 39:34.200
if I leave you lying awake
night after night?

39:39.850 --> 39:41.320
Nothing at all!

39:45.640 --> 39:47.480
Have you seen my husband?

39:52.310 --> 39:54.570
Wait here, I will look for him.

40:01.560 --> 40:04.740
You think that time heals
and walls shield,

40:06.140 --> 40:09.640
it's not true, it's not true.

40:11.140 --> 40:14.940
When things come to a head,
there is no-one pulling them up.

40:19.270 --> 40:21.990
I can't hear you,
I can't hear your voice.

40:23.180 --> 40:28.600
It's like I have drunk a bottle of anis
and I am sleeping on a bed of roses.

40:32.890 --> 40:36.440
They drag and drown me,

40:37.680 --> 40:39.350
but I swim back.

40:40.100 --> 40:41.900
Child... Child...

40:45.180 --> 40:46.940
I know I am crazy...

40:49.230 --> 40:51.740
and my heart is rotting
from holding on...

40:52.140 --> 40:54.270
You have to go right now.

40:55.270 --> 40:58.110
This will be the last time
I talk to her.

41:09.640 --> 41:11.100
I got married,

41:12.480 --> 41:14.200
you got married.

41:17.560 --> 41:19.150
It is done.

41:29.520 --> 41:31.530
Change that face...

41:36.430 --> 41:37.770
You go ahead.

41:39.230 --> 41:40.700
I'll go on horseback.

41:46.390 --> 41:48.520
Why are you looking at me like that?

41:48.850 --> 41:51.070
You sting me with your eyes.

41:51.350 --> 41:52.780
Let's go.

42:01.230 --> 42:03.080
I don't know what is happening.

42:06.310 --> 42:07.860
But I am thinking.

42:11.850 --> 42:13.700
And I don't want to think.

42:28.350 --> 42:30.360
But there is one thing I know.

42:33.100 --> 42:35.150
I am done with.

42:39.810 --> 42:41.360
And I have a child.

42:43.310 --> 42:45.280
And another on the way.

42:45.850 --> 42:47.900
Come on child.

42:48.770 --> 42:51.110
Your husband is waiting for you.

42:56.980 --> 42:58.700
Let's go! Let's go!

44:47.520 --> 44:49.400
Long live the newlyweds!

45:18.520 --> 45:21.700
Kiss her! Kiss her!

45:28.810 --> 45:31.929
Again, again, again!

45:31.930 --> 45:34.100
Again, again!

45:46.140 --> 45:47.310
Lets eat!

46:04.770 --> 46:06.030
Let's see...

46:32.430 --> 46:33.940
Thank you!

46:34.310 --> 46:36.650
- There...
- Thank you.

46:45.480 --> 46:46.820
Let me...

46:51.180 --> 46:52.980
I don't want to interrupt.

46:58.640 --> 47:00.440
Excuse me for a moment.

47:02.230 --> 47:03.450
Cousin...

47:10.680 --> 47:12.140
Congratulations.

47:12.230 --> 47:13.530
Thank you.

47:17.270 --> 47:18.900
How lovely he is.

47:20.060 --> 47:21.900
He looks like his father.

47:30.270 --> 47:31.990
Thank you for coming.

47:42.730 --> 47:44.490
The dagger, the dagger...

47:44.770 --> 47:47.530
Damn them all and the crook
that invented them.

47:47.930 --> 47:51.179
And the rifles and guns
and the smallest knife there is...

47:51.180 --> 47:52.479
Enough...

47:52.480 --> 47:55.820
All that can cut the flesh of a man,
a beautiful man...

47:56.770 --> 47:58.979
- in the prime of his life.
- Mama, be quiet.

47:58.980 --> 48:01.889
That came out of the vines,
and he didn't come back.

48:01.890 --> 48:03.390
Are you finished?

48:12.680 --> 48:13.770
Let's drink!

48:15.850 --> 48:17.280
That's what I like.

48:17.430 --> 48:20.349
Men who are men
and wheat that is wheat.

48:20.350 --> 48:23.479
<i>The olive tree, the olive tree.</i>

48:23.480 --> 48:27.180
<i>- I climbed the olive tree.</i>
- Mother, how long since you have danced?

48:27.230 --> 48:33.610
<i>And while cutting a branch
