01:07:22.810 --> 01:07:26.110
caress her in a way that provoques
just a little bit of pain,

01:07:27.180 --> 01:07:31.060
a strong embrace, a bite,
and then a soft kiss.

01:07:32.180 --> 01:07:35.929
Don't let her be upset, but let her
know that you're the man,

01:07:35.930 --> 01:07:38.520
the boss, the one who's in charge.

01:07:38.810 --> 01:07:42.710
As your father is not here, I have
to explain these things to you myself.

01:07:47.060 --> 01:07:49.360
I always do what you ask.

01:07:54.230 --> 01:07:56.110
I will go and fetch her.

01:08:00.430 --> 01:08:02.850
Where is my beautiful bride?

01:08:51.890 --> 01:08:53.599
You should be proud,
it has been a beautiful wedding,

01:08:53.600 --> 01:08:55.099
- but I must go.
- Another drink!

01:08:55.100 --> 01:08:57.429
No, no, no, another one, no.

01:08:57.430 --> 01:09:00.310
They've gone...

01:09:03.060 --> 01:09:04.450
On the horse...

01:09:06.060 --> 01:09:08.029
embraced in exhalation.

01:09:12.100 --> 01:09:14.950
Weak, delicate,

01:09:15.060 --> 01:09:17.319
a woman who doesn't sleep well...

01:09:17.600 --> 01:09:20.429
No, not my daughter.

01:09:20.430 --> 01:09:22.100
Your daughter, yes!

01:09:22.180 --> 01:09:24.770
A plant sprouted from an evil mother!

01:09:29.270 --> 01:09:31.819
But she is now my son's wife.

01:09:34.850 --> 01:09:38.450
Who has a horse, right now,
who has a horse?

01:09:38.600 --> 01:09:41.609
Who has a horse!?

01:09:42.390 --> 01:09:44.770
I'll give him whatever I have,

01:09:44.770 --> 01:09:48.279
my eyes and even my tongue...

01:09:55.270 --> 01:09:56.860
Go! After them!

01:10:00.100 --> 01:10:03.320
No. Better don't go.

01:10:03.430 --> 01:10:06.640
These people kill swiftly
and efficiently.

01:10:12.060 --> 01:10:13.490
But yes...

01:10:14.770 --> 01:10:15.950
Run!

01:10:18.350 --> 01:10:20.990
And I am coming up behind you.

01:10:34.640 --> 01:10:36.690
You and you. Go!

01:10:44.560 --> 01:10:46.150
Everybody out of here!

01:10:49.560 --> 01:10:51.740
We are going to help my son.

01:10:53.930 --> 01:10:55.350
Out of here!

01:11:00.350 --> 01:11:02.150
On all roads.

01:11:04.560 --> 01:11:07.320
The hour of blood
has arrived again...

01:11:09.560 --> 01:11:11.030
Two clans...

01:11:33.980 --> 01:11:35.740
You go to your house.

01:11:35.810 --> 01:11:38.110
Brave and alone in your home.

01:11:38.180 --> 01:11:41.520
To get old, to cry.

01:11:44.560 --> 01:11:46.280
But lock the door.

01:13:32.520 --> 01:13:33.700
Be quiet.

01:13:39.060 --> 01:13:41.110
From here, I will go alone.

01:13:41.810 --> 01:13:43.150
Go.

01:13:44.020 --> 01:13:46.700
- I want you to come back.
- I said be quiet!

01:13:46.930 --> 01:13:51.020
With your teeth, with your hands,

01:13:51.480 --> 01:13:54.979
however you can, take from
my honest neck this metal chain,

01:13:54.980 --> 01:13:57.780
leaving me forgotten there
in my earthen house.

01:13:59.520 --> 01:14:02.599
And if you don't want to kill me
as you would a little snake,

01:14:02.600 --> 01:14:05.490
put the barrel of a rifle
in my bridal hands.

01:14:06.430 --> 01:14:08.140
Ay, what lament...

01:14:09.020 --> 01:14:11.490
what a fire that rises up
through my head!

01:14:11.930 --> 01:14:14.139
How many pieces of glass
are stuck in my tongue!

01:14:14.140 --> 01:14:14.979
Be quiet!

01:14:14.980 --> 01:14:18.059
Because they are following us close
behind and I have to take you with me.

01:14:18.060 --> 01:14:21.070
- But it will have to be by force!
- By force?

01:14:21.480 --> 01:14:23.950
Who was the first
to come down the stairs?

01:14:24.060 --> 01:14:25.360
I was.

01:14:25.640 --> 01:14:27.979
Who put the bridles on the horse?

01:14:27.980 --> 01:14:30.450
I did, it's true.

01:14:31.350 --> 01:14:33.559
And whose hands
reached for my spurs?

01:14:33.560 --> 01:14:36.979
These hands,
these hands that are yours,

01:14:36.980 --> 01:14:40.059
but that upon seeing you wish
to break the murmur

01:14:40.060 --> 01:14:42.309
and blue branches of your veins.

01:14:42.310 --> 01:14:43.570
I love you!

01:14:44.180 --> 01:14:45.440
I love you!

01:14:48.140 --> 01:14:50.560
I love you! Leave me!

01:14:51.310 --> 01:14:52.530
Leave me!

01:14:58.980 --> 01:15:01.030
If I could kill you,

01:15:02.850 --> 01:15:06.070
I would cover you
with a shroud lined with violets.

01:15:08.310 --> 01:15:10.150
Ay, what grief!

01:15:10.730 --> 01:15:13.070
What fire runs through my head!

01:15:13.480 --> 01:15:16.070
What glass that cuts
through my tongue!

01:15:16.350 --> 01:15:18.450
Because I wanted to forget,

01:15:19.890 --> 01:15:22.940
so I put a stone wall between
your house and mine.

01:15:23.350 --> 01:15:24.650
It's true.

01:15:25.930 --> 01:15:27.730
Do you remember?

01:15:30.140 --> 01:15:33.019
And when I saw you from afar,
I threw sand in my eyes.

01:15:33.020 --> 01:15:36.200
But I mounted my horse and my horse
went to your door.

01:15:36.350 --> 01:15:39.610
With silver pins my blood turned black,

01:15:40.140 --> 01:15:41.640
and dreams...

01:15:42.810 --> 01:15:45.530
filled my flesh with weeds.

01:15:46.480 --> 01:15:48.360
I am not the one to blame.

01:15:48.390 --> 01:15:50.440
The blame is this land's

01:15:50.680 --> 01:15:57.480
and that perfume that rises
from your breasts and your hair.

01:15:57.890 --> 01:15:59.269
Unjust words!

01:15:59.270 --> 01:16:01.639
I don't want be your bed or food,

01:16:01.640 --> 01:16:04.889
and there isn't a minute in the day
that I don't want to be with you,

01:16:04.890 --> 01:16:09.560
because you drag me away and I go,
and you tell me to return

01:16:09.730 --> 01:16:13.110
and I follow you through the air
like a blade of grass.

01:16:45.770 --> 01:16:47.860
They won't escape.

01:16:57.020 --> 01:16:58.639
Have you seen them pass by?

01:16:58.640 --> 01:17:00.980
Over the hill.

01:17:01.140 --> 01:17:03.020
Can't you hear them?

01:17:24.890 --> 01:17:26.310
Are you sure?

01:17:54.350 --> 01:17:55.889
See this arm?

01:17:55.890 --> 01:17:57.350
It's not mine.

01:17:58.180 --> 01:18:01.560
It's the arm of my brother,
and of my father,

01:18:01.850 --> 01:18:04.200
and of all my dead family.

01:18:04.350 --> 01:18:05.700
Go...

01:18:06.270 --> 01:18:07.530
I'm going...

01:18:07.600 --> 01:18:10.809
I feel the teeth of all my people
wedged in me

01:18:10.810 --> 01:18:14.240
in a way that makes it impossible
for me to breathe calmly.

01:19:38.850 --> 01:19:42.530
I have left a good man
and all of his family...

01:19:42.640 --> 01:19:45.740
in the middle of a wedding
and with my wreath on my head.

01:19:46.020 --> 01:19:49.570
The punishment will be for you
and I don't want it to be that way.

01:19:49.600 --> 01:19:51.030
Leave me alone!

01:19:53.520 --> 01:19:54.860
Flee!

01:19:57.310 --> 01:19:59.360
There is nobody to defend you.

01:20:04.980 --> 01:20:08.200
In the trees the morning birds
are stirring.

01:20:10.310 --> 01:20:14.900
- The night is dying...
- ...on the edge of the stone.

01:20:19.270 --> 01:20:24.990
Let's go to a dark corner,
where I will always love you;

01:20:26.100 --> 01:20:30.570
I don't care about the people
or the poison they throw at us.

01:20:33.060 --> 01:20:35.400
And I will sleep at your feet

01:20:36.810 --> 01:20:39.150
to watch over your dreams.

01:20:40.560 --> 01:20:44.150
Naked, looking at the countryside.

01:20:45.390 --> 01:20:49.270
As if I were a guard dog,
because that's what I am!

01:20:51.310 --> 01:20:53.950
Look at you. Your beauty burns me.

01:20:59.310 --> 01:21:00.979
Where are you taking me?

01:21:00.980 --> 01:21:03.700
Where these men who
chase us cannot go.

01:21:06.180 --> 01:21:08.310
Where I can look at you!

01:21:10.430 --> 01:21:12.640
Take me from fair to fair,

01:21:13.850 --> 01:21:17.889
the pain of an honorable woman,
so people can see me...

01:21:17.890 --> 01:21:20.990
I would also want to leave you
if I thought as others do.

01:21:23.230 --> 01:21:25.280
But I will go wherever you go.

01:21:26.850 --> 01:21:28.110
You too.

01:21:37.770 --> 01:21:39.360
First step forward.

01:21:43.100 --> 01:21:44.150
Try.

01:21:54.890 --> 01:21:59.560
<i>In Vienna there are ten little girls</i>

01:22:00.310 --> 01:22:04.150
<i>a shoulder for death to cry on</i>

01:22:04.810 --> 01:22:09.389
<i>and a forest of dried pigeons</i>

01:22:09.390 --> 01:22:14.020
<i>There is a fragment of tomorrow</i>

01:22:14.640 --> 01:22:19.100
<i>in the museum of winter frost</i>

01:22:19.270 --> 01:22:24.280
<i>There is a thousand-windowed
dance hall</i>

01:22:24.560 --> 01:22:28.700
<i>Ay, ay, ay, ay!</i>

01:22:29.100 --> 01:22:33.950
<i>Take this waltz, take this waltz</i>

01:22:34.480 --> 01:22:40.240
<i>Take this close-mouthed waltz</i>

01:22:45.770 --> 01:22:50.530
<i>In Vienna there are four mirrors</i>

01:22:50.770 --> 01:22:55.729
<i>in which your mouth
and the echoes play</i>

01:22:55.730 --> 01:23:00.429
<i>There is a death for piano</i>

01:23:00.430 --> 01:23:05.230
<i>that paints the little boys blue</i>

01:23:05.310 --> 01:23:09.929
<i>There are beggars on the roof</i>

01:23:09.930 --> 01:23:14.730
<i>There are fresh garlands of tears</i>

01:23:15.180 --> 01:23:19.850
<i>Ay, ay, ay, ay!</i>

01:23:20.140 --> 01:23:25.440
<i>Take this waltz, take this waltz</i>

01:23:26.180 --> 01:23:32.560
<i>Take this waltz that dies in my arms</i>

01:24:16.180 --> 01:24:20.850
<i>Ay, ay, ay, ay!</i>

01:24:21.270 --> 01:24:26.570
<i>Take this waltz, take this waltz</i>

01:24:27.060 --> 01:24:33.570
<i>Take this “I will always
love you” waltz</i>

01:25:01.640 --> 01:25:05.980
<i>My soul in photographs and lilies,</i>

01:25:06.680 --> 01:25:11.020
<i>and in the dark wake
of your footsteps,</i>

01:25:12.310 --> 01:25:16.740
<i>Ay, ay, ay, ay!</i>

01:25:17.390 --> 01:25:23.060
<i>Take this waltz, take this waltz</i>

01:25:24.140 --> 01:25:30.810
<i>Take this waltz that dies in my arms</i>

01:27:41.060 --> 01:27:43.110
She is not to blame!

01:27:44.270 --> 01:27:45.530
Me neither!

01:27:46.770 --> 01:27:48.889
Whose fault is it then?

01:27:48.890 --> 01:27:51.770
Be quiet. Be quiet!

01:27:54.270 --> 01:27:55.610
Here I am.

01:27:56.390 --> 01:27:58.290
Here I am. Take vengeance on me.

01:27:58.560 --> 01:28:00.059
Look how soft my neck is;

01:28:00.060 --> 01:28:03.160
it'll be easier than cutting
a dahlia from your garden...

01:28:03.600 --> 01:28:08.240
What does your death matter to me?
What does anything matter to me?

01:28:11.350 --> 01:28:15.780
Blessed be the wheat, because
the bodies of my sons lie below it;

01:28:15.930 --> 01:28:19.560
blessed be the rain, because
it dampens the face of the dead...

01:28:20.350 --> 01:28:24.150
Blessed be the wheat, because
the bodies of my sons lie below it;

01:28:24.600 --> 01:28:28.070
blessed be the rain, because
it dampens the face of the dead...

01:28:28.230 --> 01:28:31.519
Blessed be the wheat, because
the bodies of my sons lie below it;

01:28:31.520 --> 01:28:33.929
- blessed be the rain, because...
- Have mercy on yourself.

01:28:33.930 --> 01:28:35.350
Quiet!

01:28:38.730 --> 01:28:40.320
I don't want tears.

01:28:43.980 --> 01:28:47.650
Your tears only come from your eyes.

01:28:50.390 --> 01:28:52.850
Mine come when I am alone.

01:28:53.350 --> 01:28:57.860
The spurt from the soles of my feet,
from my very roots.

01:29:14.480 --> 01:29:17.530
My son should be answering me.

01:29:20.390 --> 01:29:25.850
But my son is now
an armful of dried flowers.

01:29:41.680 --> 01:29:46.190
Come to my house,
don't stay here alone.

01:29:46.980 --> 01:29:49.320
These will be horrible days.

01:29:49.680 --> 01:29:51.690
I don't want to see anybody.

01:29:53.980 --> 01:29:55.490
The land and me.

01:29:57.060 --> 01:29:58.820
My lament and me.

01:30:00.180 --> 01:30:02.020
One must be calm.

01:30:05.980 --> 01:30:07.700
I am so poor.

01:30:08.140 --> 01:30:09.600
So poor!

01:30:09.980 --> 01:30:13.820
A woman who has no son
upon which to place her lips.

01:30:14.480 --> 01:30:16.450
Let me weep with you.

01:30:21.560 --> 01:30:22.740
Weep...

01:30:24.180 --> 01:30:25.850
but at the door.

01:31:38.600 --> 01:31:42.240
And I will follow you through the air,
like a blade of grass...

